The paper deals with medical image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of dilated convolutions and residual connections also suggests a focus on improving network architecture and training methods, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of medical imaging data, which could be categorized under neural engineering (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
